[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cyrus Christie: Derby County defender to miss "at least three months"

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Derby defender Cyrus Christie will be out for "at least three months" with a foot injury, the player has confirmed.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Christie, 24, was hurt in the first half of County's 3-2 win over Wolves, but played two minutes of the second period before being substituted.
The Republic of Ireland international has made 18 appearances this season for the Championship club.
Derby are 16th in the table, but have lost just one of their past seven league games.
